Elite French officer killed in shootout . A member of an elite French paramilitary police unit was killed during a shootout with a mentally disturbed individual in southeastern France on Monday , police said . The unidentified member of the GIGN anti - terrorism unit was the first of the elite force to be killed in service since its creation , police officials said . The officer was shot dead as police launched an assault on the deranged man ' s home , where he had been holed up since Saturday , the police said . The shootout took place in the town of Valaurie in the Drome region . The disturbed man was later seized by police and taken to a nearby psychiatric hospital , police said . 
